{
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, Figure 6 shows that this activity is often misclassified by ADL-LLM with eating-related activities and leaving home.",
    "We believe this may happen because the subject was often eating in the living room, which is also close to the main entrance door.",
    "Hence, while supervised learning baselines could recognize these activities since they have been trained with the subject's data, the general knowledge of ADL-LLM often inferred relaxing on couch when the subject spent some time in the living room.Considering the MARBLE dataset, we observe that ADL-LLM struggles in distinguishing clearing table, setting up the table, and preparing a cold meal.",
    "This is due to the lack of specific sensors characterizing these activities that involve similar actions (e.g., using the pantry, cutlery drawer, fridge).",
    "Considering taking medicines, it is correctly classified only when the windows are associated with a state related to the interaction with the medicine cabinet."
  ]
}